2 SENATE BILL 684
1 This title applies only in Harford County.
2 22–1004.
3 (a) There is:
4 (1) a 6–day Class HC (health club) beer and wine license; and
5 (2) a 7–day Class HC (health club) beer and wine license.
6 (b) The Board may issue the 6–day or the 7–day license to a person who:
7 (1) sells health club services, as defined in § 14–12B–01 of the Commercial
8 Law Article;
9 (2) has a health club facility that offers:
10 (i) an indoor or outdoor swimming pool; or
11 (ii) pickleball courts;
12 (3) has at least 150 members who pay dues; and
13 (4) owns or leases real property in the county for use as a for–profit or
14 nonprofit health club facility.
15 (c) (1) The 6–day license authorizes the license holder to sell beer and wine
16 from Monday through Saturday in a bar area at a swimming pool or an indoor lounge or
17 both.
18 (2) The 7–day license authorizes the license holder to sell beer and wine
19 from Monday through Sunday in a bar area at a swimming pool or an indoor lounge or both.
20 (d) The 6–day license holder and the 7–day license holder may sell beer and wine
21 for on–premises consumption from 1 p.m. to [9 p.m.] 11 P.M.
22 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
23 1, 2026.

